        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-7258",
        "content": "It climbs to God by trampling on Man, it builds Heaven in contempt of Earth, its soul is a phosphorescence from the slain and rotting Body; its fervent faith vilifies us worse than the coldest sneer of Mephistopheles.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-low",
